              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='9832' hidden='true' id='6' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='21775' x='17450' y='70743'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Petroleum accounts for over 97% of Australia’s energy imports, while coal and gas play a minimal role</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='12710' hidden='true' id='8' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='18615' x='11372' y='35971'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Petroleum imports show sharp spikes during global events such as the Global Financial Crisis (2008) and the Russia-Ukraine War (2022), indicating Australia&apos;s dependency on external petroleum sources</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='7514' hidden='true' id='9' story-point-id='2' type-v2='text' w='25540' x='58831' y='40448'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Coal and gas dominate Australia&apos;s energy exports, with noticeable declines during the COVID-19 and Queensland coal floods (2007)</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='7194' hidden='true' id='10' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='16331' x='16331' y='27258'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Coal dominates exports (~90%), </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>whereas Imports are so low</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='8233' hidden='true' id='11' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='19389' x='38553' y='36851'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Petroleum overwhelmingly drives imports (~97%)</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='6875' hidden='true' id='12' story-point-id='3' type-v2='text' w='20358' x='65026' y='48841'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='11'>Gas shows balanced growth compared to other categories</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' h='4297' hidden='true' id='13' story-point-id='5' type-v2='text' w='28636' x='57474' y='30081'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='12'>Between 2022-2024, Petroleum imports peaked</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
        <zone flipboard-zone-id='5' forceUpdate='true' h='8233' hidden='true' id='14' story-point-id='1' type-v2='text' w='65324' x='16555' y='16627'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='13' lmargin='600' rmargin='600'>This analysis explores Australia&apos;s energy trade within the broader Mineral Fuels, Lubricants, and Related Materials category, focusing on &quot;petroleum&quot; as the dominant subcategory, and comparing its import and export trends with coal and gas to highlight Australia&apos;s energy dependencies and trade dynamics.</run>
            <run lmargin='600' rmargin='600'>Æ&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{159CC679-F40E-4E29-83D3-D5D1B00DEC75}' />
    </dashboard>
